      "content": "I'm not a fan of those over-the-counter earwax removal drops, to be honest. They can push the wax further in, cause more irritation, or even push bacteria and other debris deeper into the ear canal, potentially leading to infection. I would strongly advise against using them, especially if you're not sure what's going on with your ear. Instead, I would recommend you to see a doctor or an ENT specialist, even if you're not sure if it's serious.",
